"ed" = (
/obj/item/paper/crumpled{
	name = "Note to Newbies";
	default_raw_text = "So you want to set up this highly unproven, absolutely unstable exotic crystal? Alright. Here’s some pointers:<br><h4>General setup</h4>Basically, we have a plasma coolant loop cooled by the thermomachines, running into the core through a heat exchanger.<br><br>We're not pulling gas out, cooling it, and pumping it back in. We're cooling the gas inside the chamber directly.<br><br><i>The actual internal gases are not moved, well except for pumping out all the crap that isn’t N² and making sure there’s enough actual N² inside.</i><br><br>I can't think about the dynamics of this for you, so pay attention to the specs:<br>-bout 101kPa<br>-somewhere around 350 mols of gas<br>-at around 90° kelvin<br><br>It's ramshackle as all hell, but it's the minimum the inspectors were willing to approve. Frankly I don't give a rat's ass about this godforsaken crystal, CC told us we're required to have it, that's the only reason I've allowed it in my station at all. Fuck.<br><br><br><br>Go fuck yourself, just use the AGCNR like a normal person.<br>Some things should not be messed with. The fabric of reality is one such thing.<br><br>Chief Engineer Brown"
	},
/obj/structure/cable/blue{
	icon_state = "1-8"
	},
/turf/open/floor/plating,
/area/engine/engine_room)
