	icon_state = "1-2"
	},
/obj/item/paper/guides{
	name = "Electrical Primer";
	pixel_y = 3;
	default_raw_text = "<b><center><h1>Primer<br></h1><h3>The Lair Station electrical system.</h3></center><br><h3>- Quickstart Checklist:</h3>- 1. Start the reactor and stabilise it around 1-2MW.<br> - 2. Check that all the SMES are accounted for on the reactor power console.<br> - 3. Visit each of the SMES in order and set their in/outputs accordingly.<br> - 4. Re-check that the reactor is giving adequate power, adjust if necessary.<br><br><h3>- The Grid:</h3>In similar station setups, a central SMES reservoir feeds one large wire-loop connecting every APC. <i>This is not what we are doing here.</i><br><br>Here, the primary reactor output is pumped directly through yellow wires in maintenance, feeding local substations on every level. These substations supply power to either the entire level, or separate departments, usually through blue wiring. A list of substations can be found at the bottom of this page.<br><br><h3>- The Reactor:</h3>The Advanced Gas Cooled Nuclear Reactor, or AGCNR, works by injecting fissionable fuel cells with reactive plasma or other fuel gasses. Refer to the standarg guidebook for general advice. Here are some tips for this setup specifically:<br><br> - Before doing anything else, pressurize the fuel line to approximately 3000 kPa of 20° nitrogen. The reservoir tank is ideal for this. To do so, open the coolant line valve and set the "CoolanttoCore" pump to 3000 kPa.<br><br><i>This is a great way to ensure a static amount of coolant in the system, limiting potential pressure hazards.</i><br><br> - Make sure not to run the moderator line at full power, this is really not needed and wastes most of the gas. 1500kPa at the inlet is fine.<br><h3>- Substation List:</h3>";
	color = "#ffad00"
	},
/turf/open/floor/iron/smooth,
/area/lair/engineering/control)
